{
  "text": "Developmental changes in the properties of stem cells have been best described in hematopoiesis [CITATION_1] . Fetal HSCs differ from adult HSCs in gene expression [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , marker expression [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , developmental potential [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] , self-renewal potential [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] , and regulation [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . HSCs transition from fetal to adult properties 3-4 weeks after birth, when HSCs suddenly become quiescent [CITATION_12] .",
